'''Napoleon Antionette''' (1890 - c. 1960s) was a French Foreign Legion soldier who served as an enlistee during World War I and as an officer during World War II and the Korean War. He is widely known as the stepfather of French politician and Navy sailor [[Kylian Morin (V1.2)|Kylian Morin]]. 

==Early life==
Napoleon was born in France in 1890 to a caring and prominent family of French nobles. According to most sources, his parents named him after Napoleon Bonaparte.

